  "prompt": "What are some locations in Tennessee that are suitable for a prom?",
  "response": "Tennessee offers a wide range of venues perfect for a prom, depending on your budget, theme, and preferred vibe. Here are some ideas categorized by type and location:\n\n**Nashville & Middle Tennessee:**\n\n*   **For a Glamorous & Elegant Prom:**\n    *   **The Bridge Building (Nashville):** Offers stunning views of the Nashville skyline and a modern, industrial-chic vibe.\n    *   **Cheekwood Botanical Garden & Museum of Art (Nashville):** Provides a beautiful and sophisticated setting with gardens and elegant spaces.\n    *   **The Parthenon (Nashville):** A unique and iconic landmark offering a memorable backdrop for photos.\n    *   **Country Music Hall of Fame and Museum (Nashville):** If your school loves country music, this could be a really unique option.\n    *   **The Factory at Franklin (Franklin):** A historic factory with unique event spaces and industrial charm.\n\n*   **For a Modern & Trendy Prom:**\n    *   **Pinewood Social (Nashville):** Offers a fun and versatile space with bowling lanes, a restaurant, and outdoor areas.\n    *   **The Cordelle (Nashville):** A historic event space with a modern and elegant design.\n    *   **OZ Arts Nashville (Nashville):** A contemporary art center that can be transformed into a unique event space.\n\n*   **For a Rustic & Outdoor Prom:**\n    *   **Arrington Vineyards (Arrington):** A beautiful vineyard setting with rolling hills and stunning views.\n    *   **Southall Farm & Inn (Franklin):** Offers a luxurious farm experience with beautiful barns and outdoor spaces.\n\n**Memphis & West Tennessee:**\n\n*   **For a Historic & Grand Prom:**\n    *   **The Cadre Building (Memphis):** A historic bank building with ornate details and grand ballrooms.\n    *   **Dixon Gallery & Gardens (Memphis):** Features beautiful gardens and art galleries for a sophisticated event.\n\n*   **For a Unique & Musical Prom:**\n    *   **Graceland (Memphis):** A legendary venue that offers a rock 'n' roll twist.\n    *   **Stax Museum of American Soul Music (Memphis):** Perfect for a soul music-themed prom.\n\n*   **For a Modern & Stylish Prom:**\n    *   **The Columns at One Commerce Square (Memphis):** A modern event space with a sleek and contemporary design.\n\n**Knoxville & East Tennessee:**\n\n*   **For a Scenic & Outdoor Prom:**\n    *   **Hunter Valley Farm (Knoxville):** A beautiful farm with rolling hills, barns, and outdoor spaces.\n    *   **Ijams Nature Center (Knoxville):** Offers a natural setting for a unique and eco-friendly prom.\n\n*   **For a Historic & Charming Prom:**\n    *   **The Mill & Mine (Knoxville):** A historic industrial space that has been renovated into a modern event venue.\n\n*   **For a Downtown & Urban Prom:**\n    *   **World's Fair Park (Knoxville):** Offers a variety of spaces, including outdoor areas and the Sunsphere.\n    *   **Knoxville Museum of Art (Knoxville):** Offers a sophisticated and artistic setting.\n\n**Other Considerations When Choosing a Venue:**\n\n*   **Budget:** Determine how much your school is willing to spend on the venue.\n*   **Capacity:** Make sure the venue can accommodate the expected number of students and chaperones.\n*   **Accessibility:** Consider accessibility for students with disabilities.\n*   **Parking:** Ensure there is ample parking for attendees.\n*   **Catering:** Some venues have in-house catering, while others allow you to bring in your own caterer.\n*   **Decorations:** Check the venue's policies on decorations and ensure they align with your theme.\n*   **Security:** Ensure adequate security measures are in place.\n*   **Availability:** Book the venue well in advance, as popular locations can fill up quickly.\n*   **Insurance:**  Make sure the venue (or your school) has adequate insurance coverage.\n*   **Reviews:**  Read online reviews of the venue to get a sense of its reputation.\n\n**To find more specific options:**\n\n*   **Search online event venue directories:** Websites like The Knot, WeddingWire, and Eventbrite often have listings of event venues in Tennessee.\n*   **Contact local event planners:** Event planners can help you find venues that meet your specific needs and budget.\n*   **Check with local hotels:** Hotels often have ballrooms and event spaces that are suitable for proms.\n*   **Ask for recommendations:** Talk to other schools or organizations that have hosted proms in the area.\n\nRemember to visit potential venues in person to get a better sense of their suitability for your prom.  Good luck with your planning!\n",
